            <entry xml:id="entry_aldymbyd" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d177e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aldymbyd</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d177e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aldæmbid</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d177e72">
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d177e73">
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тесьма шелковая</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>silk ribbon, trim</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </sense>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d177e82">
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>галун (которым обшивают края черкески, башлыка, чувяков, ноговиц и
                                пр.)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>galloon (which is used to welt the edges of a Circassian coat,
                                bashlyk, chuvyaks, gaiters, etc.)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </sense>
                </sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d177e92">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d177e94">
                        <quote>aldymbyd x˳ydtoj cūqqajy æmæ k˳yræty kærættyl, kodtoj ʒy
                            aǧnæǵytæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тесьмой <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">aldymbyd</hi> обшивали края
                                черкески и бешмета, делали из нее пуговицы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the trim <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">aldymbyd</hi> was used to
                                welt the edges of the Circassian coat and beshmet, buttons were made
                                out of it</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d177e109">
                        <quote>dambacabos jæ q˳yryl kond, jæ q˳ymbyltæ — aldymbydæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>шнурок от пистолета надет на его шею, его (шнурка) узлы (сделаны) из
                                шелковой тесьмы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a pistol string is put on his neck, its (lace) knots are (made) of
                                silk braid</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"/>
                            <biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Так как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byd"/> | <hi rendition="#rend_italic">bid</hi> (q. v.) значит уже ‘тесьма’, то под <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldym-byd</hi> разумелся, очевидно, какой-то особый
                    вид тесьмы или галуна; мы предтолагаем, что имелся в виду позолоченный галун
                    (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærdgæbyd"/>), и в первой части <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldym</hi> (← <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldyn</hi>-) видим <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e230" xml:id="mentioned_d177e135" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>altən</w>
                        <gloss><q>золото</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e238" xml:id="mentioned_d177e143" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>золотой</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e244" xml:id="mentioned_d177e149" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>altən-čalu</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (где <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e250" xml:id="mentioned_d177e155" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                                <w>čalu</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">—</note>
                                <gloss><q>тесьма</q></gloss></mentioned>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>галун</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для эволюции значения ср.
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e265" xml:id="mentioned_d177e170" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(с персидского)
                        </note><w>zarnavuxt</w></mentioned>, первоначально ‘златотканный’,
                    впоследствии вообще ‘шелковый’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I 149
                            сл.</biblScope></bibl>); эволюция значения <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e277" xml:id="mentioned_d177e182" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>алтын</w></mentioned> в русском такого же порядка; ср. также по типу
                    сложения <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e282" xml:id="mentioned_d177e187" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(с персидского) </note><w>zarbafta</w>
                        <gloss><q>галун</q></gloss></mentioned>, буквально ‘златотканный’. Почему в
                    первой части композиции в значении ‘золотой’ использовано <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e292" xml:id="mentioned_d177e197" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>altən</w></mentioned>, а не свое <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zærīn"/>
                    (ср. <hi rendition="#rend_italic">zærin-bos</hi> ‘золотой шнур’, <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 150,
                        151</biblScope></bibl>), — объясняется, надо думать, историей
                    соответствующих реалий, для установления которой мы, к сожалению, не располагаем
                    данными. Характерно, что в <hi rendition="#rend_bold">сербском</hi> в сложных
                    словах в значении <q>золотой</q> используется усвоенное из турецкого <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e304" xml:id="mentioned_d177e209" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>aldum-</w></mentioned> наряду со <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e309" xml:id="mentioned_d177e214" xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">злато-</w></mentioned>. В осетинском можно указать еще пример
                    сложения тюркского слова с осетинским: <hi rendition="#rend_italic">tin-kærc</hi> ‘беличья шуба’, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīn"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Since <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byd"/> | <hi rendition="#rend_italic">bid</hi> (q. v.) means <q>trim</q>, then <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldym-byd</hi> obviously meant some special kind of
                    trim or galoon; we assume that a gold covered galoon was meant (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xærdgæbyd"/>), and in the first part <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldym</hi> (← <hi rendition="#rend_italic">aldyn</hi>-) we see <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e135" xml:id="mentioned_d177e230" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>altən</w>
                        <gloss><q>gold</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e143" xml:id="mentioned_d177e238" xml:lang="trk"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>golden</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e149" xml:id="mentioned_d177e244" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>altən-čalu</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (where <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e155" xml:id="mentioned_d177e250" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                                <w>čalu</w>
                                <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">—</note>
                                <gloss><q>braid</q></gloss></mentioned>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>galoon</q></gloss></mentioned>. For the evolution of the meaning
                    cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e170" xml:id="mentioned_d177e265" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Persian)
                        </note><w>zarnavuxt</w></mentioned>, initially ‘gold-brocaded’, later even
                    ‘silk’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."/><biblScope xml:lang="en">I 149 ff.</biblScope></bibl>); the evolution of the
                    meaning of <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e182" xml:id="mentioned_d177e277" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>altyn</w></mentioned> is the same in Russian; cf. also by the type of
                    compound <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e187" xml:id="mentioned_d177e282" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Persian)</note>
                        <w>zarbafta</w>
                        <gloss><q>galoon</q></gloss></mentioned>, literally ‘gold-brocaded’. The
                    fact that <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e197" xml:id="mentioned_d177e292" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>altən</w></mentioned> is used in the meaning ‘golden’ in the first part,
                    and not Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zærīn"/> (cf. <hi rendition="#rend_italic">zærin-bos</hi> ‘golden cord’, <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 150,
                        151</biblScope></bibl>), is explained by the history of the corresponding
                    realities, which, unfortunately, we cannot establish due to lack of data. It is
                    significant that in <hi rendition="#rend_bold">Serbian</hi> in compounds
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e209" xml:id="mentioned_d177e304" xml:lang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>aldum-</w></mentioned>, borrowed from Turkish, is used in the meaning
                    ‘golden’ as well as <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d177e214" xml:id="mentioned_d177e309" xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>zlato-</w></mentioned>. In Ossetic one can indicate another example of
                    the composing a Turkic word with an Ossetic one: <hi rendition="#rend_italic">tin-kærc</hi> ‘squirrel fur coat’, see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīn"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
